*{{GRD}}：1989年7月20日与[[中華民國|中华民国]]建交<ref>{{Cite web|title=1989-07-29第1版面所有文章内容 - 人民日报1946-2003 - 老资料网|url=http://www.laoziliao.net/rmrb/1989-07-29-1#835498|accessdate=2021-03-04|work=www.laoziliao.net}}</ref>，7月31日中华民国在格林纳达设立大使馆，8月7日格林纳达与[[中華人民共和國|中华人民共和国]]断交<ref>{{Cite web|title=1989-08-07第1版面所有文章内容 - 人民日报1946-2003 - 老资料网|url=http://www.laoziliao.net/rmrb/1989-08-07-1#836350|accessdate=2021-03-04|work=www.laoziliao.net}}</ref><ref name=":13">{{Cite book|chapter=Chapter One Introdution|url=https://books.google.co.kr/books?id=7nm6DwAAQBAJ&pg=PA6&lpg=PA6&dq=grenada+1989+tiananmen+massacre&source=bl&ots=2_opSd4pxY&sig=ACfU3U1YUr8uTE0h2NJUwNIjalTTfUOSFA&hl=zh-CN&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjy3Kylx5nvAhVTVN4KHf78DoEQ6AEwGHoECA8QAw#v=onepage&q=grenada%201989%20tiananmen%20massacre&f=false|publisher=Rowman & Littlefield|date=2019-11-15|isbn=978-1-7936-0323-4|language=en|first=Theodor|last=Tudoroiu|title=The Myth of China’s No Strings Attached Development Assistance: A Caribbean Case Study|quote=Their genuine repulsion for brutal antidemocratic practices and their interest in China's situation is illustrated by  Grenada's and Berlize's recognization of Taiwan in response to the Tiananmen massacre(Hu 2015: 11)}}</ref><ref name=":14">{{Cite web|title=The Impact of Tiananmen on China's Foreign Policy|url=https://www.nbr.org/publication/the-impact-of-tiananmen-on-chinas-foreign-policy/|accessdate=2021-03-05|work=The National Bureau of Asian Research (NBR)|language=en|quote=At first, China’s Third World orientation appeared to gain little success. In 1989, in fact, Beijing’s efforts to maintain ties with Asia, Africa, and Latin America were overshadowed by the decisions of such countries as Grenada, Belize, and Liberia to extend diplomatic recognition to Taiwan.|archive-date=2021-09-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210904072706/https://www.nbr.org/publication/the-impact-of-tiananmen-on-chinas-foreign-policy/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Tiananmen: The View from Ta